This paper is about hyperparameter optimization in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper specifically addresses the challenge of finding a good combination of hyperparameters for a machine learning system. Other likely categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these sub-categories are also relevant to machine learning and optimization.
